One of the best experiences to be had in Hong Kong. In 45 minutes, the junk sails to Central and back, where you'll see amazing night view Hong Kong harbour. Highly recommended.
There's no need to get tickets to the sky terrace. There are two free options to get vantage view. One is the Lion View Point. The other is the rooftop of the building opposite.

tip.text: Quite an hidden gem in Murrumbena. Try the Rambo burger on specials!
The lamb bagel just is amazing! Don't miss out!
You will find all the usual suspects plus a few really special and authentic Malaysian dishes. For example this Penang Char Kiu Teow with duck egg!
Some happiness we have here
Consistently wonderful long macchiato!
Go up to the balcony for a view down the central arteries of Melbourne CBD. This is a truly impressive monument!
A truly exceptional dining experience. Really big dining area indoor and outdoor. Food wise, please do try crispy pancake, duck curry and sweet potato fritters!
Food is well presented and tastes good when they come. The staff is still a bit disorganized and waiting time can be very long when they are busy. Give them a couple of weeks before visiting.
An amazing place to have a picnic at any spot of the massive lawn everywhere. Perfect way to spend a lazy Saturday afternoon.
Surprisingly pleasant place to walk around. Good place for self reflection.
Wifi is available for everyone. Come in for a moment of peace. Magazine rack is located just to the right after the entrance.
Service is good most of the time. Sugar cane prawn is a highlight.
Long macchiato with a side of milk is a nice touch.
While the juices are deliciously healthy, you pay a premium for it. Around $7.5-$9.5 for 475ml bottle.
San Telmo cafe. Early bird special 8-9am: $3 coffee
